#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Rule "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Kinnusīhasutta → sīhasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | sīho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Kinnusīhasutta "
msgstr "12. Lion "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn4.12:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "sn4.12:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ deseti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time the Buddha was teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large assembly. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.110, pts2ed1.245, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.12:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Māra thought, "

msgctxt "sn4.12:2.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ deseti. "
msgstr "“The ascetic Gotama is teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large assembly. "

# NOTE: This phrase is more idiomatic than I prefer, but here it captues both the literal sense and the meaning better than any more formal phrase.
msgctxt "sn4.12:2.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ vicakkhukammāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go and pull the wool over their eyes?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.12:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.1"
msgid "“Kinnu sīhova nadasi, "
msgstr "“Why now do you roar like a lion? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.2"
msgid "parisāyaṃ visārado; "
msgstr "You’re so self-assured in the assembly! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.3"
msgid "Paṭimallo hi te atthi, "
msgstr "For there is someone who’ll wrestle with you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.4"
msgid "vijitāvī nu maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "so why do you imagine you’re the victor?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.1"
msgid "“Nadanti ve mahāvīrā, "
msgstr "“The great heroes they roar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.2"
msgid "parisāsu visāradā; "
msgstr "self-assured in the assembly. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.3"
msgid "Tathāgatā balappattā, "
msgstr "The Realized One, attained to power, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.4"
msgid "tiṇṇā loke visattikan”ti. "
msgstr "has crossed over clinging to the world.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.12:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
